benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/block - Block an account

covered: Valid Payload: Successful creation of BlockingState with valid payload across scenarios TC01-TC05, TC15-TC17, TC18
Invalid Payload: Tests for missing body (TC09), malformed JSON (TC10), malicious payload (TC14)
Duplicate Submission: Regression test preventing duplicate BlockingState (TC23)
Large Payloads: Large payload handling near limit (TC20)
Validation: Edge cases with max/min fields and empty arrays (TC16, TC17, TC15)
Server Error Handling: Database unavailable leads to 503 (TC12)
gaps: Rate Limiting: No tests for rate limiting or throttling on POST
Caching Behavior: No tests around caching headers or cache invalidation for POST responses
Invalid Data Types: Not explicit tests for incorrect data types within BlockingState fields beyond length constraints
Internal Server Error variants: Only 503 for DB down; add 500 for generic server errors
recommendations: Add tests to validate caching headers (Cache-Control, ETag) on POST responses if applicable
Add tests covering invalid data types in BlockingState payload
Add 500 Internal Server Error scenario simulations
Extend authorization tests to cover invalid/expired tokens
Include accessibility considerations in API responses beyond docs
